Package: GOAnno4Bioc
Title: Modular Gene Ontology Annotation Parsing for Bioconductor
Version: 0.0.3
Authors@R:
    person("Vincent", "Carey", email = "stvjc@channing.harvard.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4046-0063"))
Description: Provides modular, tidy tools for parsing and working with Gene
    Ontology Annotation Format (GAF) files.  Intended as infrastructure for
    building species-specific annotation packages, replacing the tightly coupled
    org.*.eg.db model with a composable approach: GAF files are parsed into
    tibbles with explicit RO predicate mappings derived from the GAF Aspect
    field, cached via BiocFileCache, and convertible to the semsql
    term_association schema for use with GO.ddb.  Cross-references to Entrez,
    Ensembl, UniProt, and other identifier spaces are handled as separate
    modular lookups rather than pre-joined monolithic databases.
